The command for backing up the databse to an SQL or Archive file is:


pg_dump abet_system_dev > abet_sys_dev_backup.sql

NOTE: abet_system_dev is just the name of the database.
      abet_sys_dev_backup.sql is the name of the file to be saved.


User Story 15 requests to save backups of the database every week. By using this command, we instruct npm
to dump the database to a file saved locally.
